#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.77"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.77:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.77:0.2"
msgid "8. Yamakavagga "
msgstr "8. Pairs "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an8.77:0.3"
msgid "77. Icchāsutta "
msgstr "77. Desires "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an8.77:1.1"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "an8.77:1.2"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.77:1.3"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied. "

msgctxt "an8.77:1.4"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca: "
msgstr "Sāriputta said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.326, sc2
msgctxt "an8.77:2.1"
msgid "“Aṭṭhime, āvuso, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Reverends, these eight people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an8.77:2.2"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha? "
msgstr "What eight? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.77:2.3"
msgid "Idhāvuso, bhikkhuno pavivittassa viharato nirāyattavuttino icchā uppajjati lābhāya. "
msgstr "First, when a mendicant stays secluded, living independently, a desire arises for material possessions. "

msgctxt "an8.77:2.4"
msgid "So uṭṭhahati, ghaṭati, vāyamati lābhāya. "
msgstr "They try hard, strive, and make an effort to get them. "

msgctxt "an8.77:2.5"
msgid "Tassa uṭṭhahato, ghaṭato, vāyamato lābhāya lābho nuppajjati. "
msgstr "But material possessions don’t come to them. "

msgctxt "an8.77:2.6"
msgid "So tena alābhena socati kilamati paridevati, urattāḷiṃ kandati, sammohaṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "And so they sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion because they don’t get those material possessions. "

msgctxt "an8.77:2.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccatāvuso, ‘bhikkhu iccho viharati lābhāya, uṭṭhahati, ghaṭati, vāyamati lābhāya, na ca lābhī, socī ca paridevī ca, cuto ca saddhammā’. (1) "
msgstr "This is called a mendicant who lives desiring material possessions. They try hard, strive, and make an effort to get them. But when possessions don’t come to them, they sorrow and lament. They’ve fallen from the true teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
